did.abstract: Speeches and writings, correspondence, notes, printed matter, phonotapes, phonorecords, and photographs, relating to philosophy, the nature of knowledge, the philosophy of culture, the philosophy and methodology of science, and the philosophy of history and the social sciences. Deacribed in two groups, original collection (boxes 1-463) and the incremental materials acquired at a later date (boxes 464-583).

physdesc.label: Collection Size
physdesc.extent: 575 manuscript boxes, 6 oversize boxes, 2 card file boxes, 28 envelopes, 47 phonotape reels, 4 phonotape cassettes, 11 phonorecords

accessrestrict.p: Microfilm use only. Use copies of sound recordings are available for immediate use.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Acquired by the Hoover Institution Archives in 1986 with increments added at a later date.

accruals.head: Accruals
accruals.p: Materials may have been added to the collection since this finding aid was prepared. To determine if this has occurred, find the collection in Stanford University's online catalog at http://searchworks.stanford.edu/. scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: Speeches and writings, correspondence, notes, printed matter, phonotapes, phonorecords, and photographs, relating to philosophy, the nature of knowledge, the philosophy of culture, the philosophy and methodology of science, and the philosophy of history and the social sciences. Most of collection also available on microfilm (564 reels). Sound use copies of sound recordings available.
